  <summary date="2003-11-20T20:16:58Z" status="Introduced in Senate">Border Security and Immigration Improvement Act - Amends the Immigration and Nationality Act to establish new visa programs for: (1) aliens who seek to enter the United States as temporary workers; and (2) undocumented aliens residing in the United States who seek to remain legally in the United States.

Authorizes additional funding for the United States Employment Service to assist States meet increased employment services resulting from the amendments made by this Act.</summary>
